      • writeMetaDataSoundZip

        void writeMetaDataSoundZip(List<String> setIDs,
                           OutputStream output)
                    throws StorageException
        Collect the sounds contained in the sets with the given ids as .wav files into the stream representing a zip file and include a metadata.csv file that specifies the labels for the sounds. The names of the files in the zip are either the name assigned in storage (with additional indexing. if duplicate names are found) or the id of the sound if a name is not assigned. In either case .wav is appended if not present.
        Parameters:
        setIDs - ids of sets to export
        output - stream to which zipped bytes are written. Caller must close the stream.
        Throws:
        StorageException

      • addMetaDataSoundZip

        List<String> addMetaDataSoundZip(String setID,
                                 InputStream zipStream)
                          throws StorageException,
                                 IOException
        Add 0 or more SegmentedSoundRecordings contained in the given byte array representing a zip of wav files and a metadata.csv
        Parameters:
        setID - the destination set to receive the added sounds.
        zipStream - the input stream containing the bytes to unzip. Caller must close the stream.
        Returns:
        a list of ids, one for each sound added to storage.
        Throws:
        StorageException - if all sounds could not be added.
        IOException - if zippedSounds is not a zip.
